# Playwright Network

Use network control when the page behavior depends on API calls or third-party resources.

```typescript
await page.route('**/api/products', async route => {
  await route.fulfill({
    status: 200,
    contentType: 'application/json',
    body: JSON.stringify([{ id: 'p1', name: 'Widget' }])
  });
});

const responsePromise = page.waitForResponse('**/api/products');
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Refresh' }).click();
const response = await responsePromise;
expect(response.status()).toBe(200);
```

Routes are evaluated before matching requests are sent. Register routes before navigating or before the action that triggers the request.
